53
00:04:11,183 --> 00:04:14,283
to make this very special dish.

54
00:04:27,217 --> 00:04:28,983
Go ahead.

55
00:04:29,717 --> 00:04:31,417
Okay.

56
00:04:55,250 --> 00:04:57,350
Wow.

57
00:05:06,283 --> 00:05:07,617
Yum, good.

58
00:05:07,617 --> 00:05:09,217
Alright.

59
00:05:13,717 --> 00:05:16,417
The japchae is delicious.

60
00:05:20,050 --> 00:05:21,850
Bulgogi.

61
00:05:25,317 --> 00:05:27,417
It's tasty, so tasty!

62
00:05:29,450 --> 00:05:33,050
By the way, who is he?

63
00:05:33,050 --> 00:05:34,583
Oh,

64
00:05:34,583 --> 00:05:35,983
I forgot to introduce him.

65
00:05:35,983 --> 00:05:37,183
He is...

66
00:05:37,183 --> 00:05:39,083
Took you long enough to ask who I am.

67
00:05:39,083 --> 00:05:43,083
Oh, I'm sorry, I was distracted.

68
00:05:43,083 --> 00:05:44,383
Let's finish eating first.

69
00:05:44,383 --> 00:05:46,317
It tastes bad when cold.

70
00:05:49,850 --> 00:05:53,417
Wow, nice trees.

71
00:05:53,417 --> 00:05:55,250
Oh my, Driver Lee.

72
00:05:55,250 --> 00:05:57,783
You ate three bowls of rice, huh?

73
00:05:57,783 --> 00:05:59,217
I have to drive again when I leave, you know.

74
00:05:59,217 --> 00:06:02,550
Oh my, look here, guys!

75
00:06:02,550 --> 00:06:03,550
Omija berries.

76
00:06:03,550 --> 00:06:07,983
It should be hanging like this, see?

77
00:06:10,783 --> 00:06:15,317
Ah, you met that lady

78
00:06:15,317 --> 00:06:16,417
here?

79
00:06:16,417 --> 00:06:18,417
Oh, right.

80
00:06:18,417 --> 00:06:20,950
- I filmed it.
- Yeah.

81
00:06:20,950 --> 00:06:22,883
- Here.
<i>- That tree right there</i>

82
00:06:22,883 --> 00:06:24,883
<i>is the prayer bead tree.</i>

83
00:06:26,850 --> 00:06:28,083
<i>Huh?</i>

84
00:06:28,083 --> 00:06:30,083
<i>Someone's there?</i>

85
00:06:30,083 --> 00:06:33,117
<i>Did they come to see the prayer bead tree like us?</i>

86
00:06:36,617 --> 00:06:38,383
I don't see anyone.

87
00:06:38,383 --> 00:06:39,883
Too small.

88
00:06:39,883 --> 00:06:42,483
I'm not used to filming...

89
00:06:42,483 --> 00:06:46,250
But, she looked exactly the same.

90
00:06:46,250 --> 00:06:48,850
That doesn't make sense.

91
00:06:48,850 --> 00:06:50,283
Someone from America

92
00:06:50,283 --> 00:06:52,583
being here, how?

93
00:06:52,583 --> 00:06:54,417
Unless...

94
00:06:54,417 --> 00:06:56,083
A twin?

95
00:06:56,917 --> 00:06:58,617
Did they fight?

96
00:07:00,083 --> 00:07:02,050
I guess they fought. They really fought.

97
00:07:02,050 --> 00:07:06,383
Even siblings become worse than
strangers when they fight.

98
00:07:06,383 --> 00:07:08,950
Is that from your own experience, Mr. O?

99
00:07:11,850 --> 00:07:13,650
Refreshing.

100
00:07:13,650 --> 00:07:17,117
She said she has never been to Korea before.

101
00:07:17,117 --> 00:07:18,917
Ah, right.

102
00:07:21,583 --> 00:07:23,917
Just ask her straight up.

103
00:07:23,917 --> 00:07:27,350
'Someone who looks exactly
like you live in the US.'

104
00:07:27,350 --> 00:07:29,617
'But, she asked us to travel here instead.'

105
00:07:29,617 --> 00:07:30,917
'Do you know her?'

106
00:07:30,917 --> 00:07:32,450
Ask her yourself.

107
00:07:32,450 --> 00:07:33,517
Come on.

108
00:07:33,517 --> 00:07:35,717
Without even knowing the story,

109
00:07:35,717 --> 00:07:39,217
I wondered if it would be
okay to just ask like that.

110
00:07:39,217 --> 00:07:40,950
Right.

111
00:08:11,758 --> 00:08:13,917
Okay.

112
00:08:13,917 --> 00:08:16,150
Can you really do this?

113
00:08:16,150 --> 00:08:17,850
Are you not going back with us?

114
00:08:18,583 --> 00:08:21,883
I came all this way, so I should finish properly.

115
00:08:23,217 --> 00:08:25,417
You're back, huh?

116
00:08:25,417 --> 00:08:27,683
That country girl from Hwado,

117
00:08:27,683 --> 00:08:30,150
who was away for a bit, is back.

118
00:08:30,150 --> 00:08:31,783
The fearless spirit!

119
00:08:32,817 --> 00:08:35,483
I'm tired of hearing that all the time.

120
00:08:35,483 --> 00:08:38,250
Ah, about that... when will you tell me?

121
00:08:38,250 --> 00:08:41,017
Why did you cast the clueless country girl
who came on a school trip

122
00:08:41,017 --> 00:08:43,383
to Seoul from the countryside?

123
00:08:48,683 --> 00:08:51,117
<i>Ugh, it's tough.</i>

124
00:08:51,117 --> 00:08:54,883
<i>Where should I go, O Sang Sik?</i>

125
00:08:54,883 --> 00:08:56,783
<i>Mister,</i>

126
00:08:59,083 --> 00:09:02,050
<i>did you get lost, too?</i>

127
00:09:03,550 --> 00:09:05,150
<i>Huh?</i>

128
00:09:09,417 --> 00:09:12,217
Hey, I'll go.

129
00:09:15,183 --> 00:09:18,650
Oh, that... your phone.

130
00:09:18,650 --> 00:09:19,917
Never mind.

131
00:09:19,917 --> 00:09:21,550
I'll go.

132
00:09:39,517 --> 00:09:41,350
Let's go!

133
00:09:41,350 --> 00:09:42,650
Let's just do one more thing before leaving.

134
00:09:42,650 --> 00:09:43,883
What else?

135
00:09:43,883 --> 00:09:45,417
- Wait a second...
- Don't.

136
00:09:45,417 --> 00:09:47,117
Hey, Driver Lee!

137
00:09:48,250 --> 00:09:50,783
Travel is about experiencing
with all five senses, right?

138
00:09:50,783 --> 00:09:53,283
Sound matters too.

139
00:09:53,283 --> 00:09:57,750
If you film without a mic,
ambient noise ruins the audio.

140
00:09:57,750 --> 00:10:01,717
In TV editing, you can remove
noise and add music later,

141
00:10:01,717 --> 00:10:05,083
but travel videos need authentic nature sounds.

142
00:10:06,017 --> 00:10:10,283
Clip this on like, and...

143
00:10:11,017 --> 00:10:13,483
use it this way.

144
00:10:13,483 --> 00:10:15,083
It's simple.

145
00:10:15,983 --> 00:10:18,617
And this is called a windshield.

146
00:10:18,617 --> 00:10:21,017
It's useful when the weather is bad.

147
00:10:21,017 --> 00:10:24,583
Wow, that's amazing.

148
00:10:24,583 --> 00:10:26,317
Don't say that.

149
00:10:26,317 --> 00:10:27,717
It's fascinating, though.

150
00:10:27,717 --> 00:10:30,583
Feels like I became an expert overnight.

151
00:10:30,583 --> 00:10:32,517
Thank you.

152
00:10:32,517 --> 00:10:34,850
Really thank you, Yeon Seok oppa.

153
00:10:36,317 --> 00:10:37,950
Oppa?

154
00:10:38,650 --> 00:10:40,650
Can I call you oppa?

155
00:10:40,650 --> 00:10:42,317
Yeah.

156
00:10:42,317 --> 00:10:44,683
Can't keep calling you 'mister,' right?

157
00:10:46,950 --> 00:10:49,650
What's up with that punk?

158
00:10:49,650 --> 00:10:51,583
Why's he staring like that?

159
00:10:51,583 --> 00:10:54,517
How dare he...

160
00:10:55,650 --> 00:10:56,750
Why is he looking at her that way?

161
00:10:56,750 --> 00:10:58,317
I want to show this off.

162
00:10:58,317 --> 00:11:00,150
Mr. O!

163
00:11:00,150 --> 00:11:03,450
Mr. O!

164
00:11:03,450 --> 00:11:05,183
- Why does he have to do this?
- Look at this.

165
00:11:05,183 --> 00:11:06,483
Look at this.

166
00:11:06,483 --> 00:11:08,250
Oppa...

167
00:11:16,683 --> 00:11:20,083
If you have something to say, just say it.

168
00:11:20,878 --> 00:11:23,417
Hmph.

169
00:11:23,417 --> 00:11:25,134
You seem excited today, huh?

170
00:11:25,134 --> 00:11:26,158
Me?

171
00:11:26,158 --> 00:11:27,214
You're humming.

172
00:11:27,214 --> 00:11:28,283
You are like, 'Me?' and stuff.

173
00:11:28,283 --> 00:11:30,417
- No, I'm not.
- Yeah, la la la.

174
00:11:30,417 --> 00:11:33,817
I actually get hyped when driving.

175
00:11:33,817 --> 00:11:35,650
You didn't say a word

176
00:11:35,650 --> 00:11:37,950
or crack a smile the whole ride here with me,

177
00:11:37,950 --> 00:11:39,083
so what nonsense is that?

178
00:11:39,083 --> 00:11:41,517
Spending time with you

179
00:11:41,517 --> 00:11:43,017
brings some excitement, too.

180
00:11:43,017 --> 00:11:45,850
'Spending time with you
brings some excitement, too.'

181
00:11:45,850 --> 00:11:49,150
Geez, you're really hyped.

182
00:11:49,150 --> 00:11:51,383
No wonder you just went along

183
00:11:51,383 --> 00:11:53,150
when I said we should go together.

184
00:11:53,150 --> 00:11:55,450
I've been thinking, Mr. O.

185
00:11:55,450 --> 00:11:56,617
Hmph.

186
00:11:56,617 --> 00:11:57,717
What thought?

187
00:11:57,717 --> 00:11:58,750
Huh?

188
00:11:58,750 --> 00:12:01,817
Why such a negative response
without even hearing me out?

189
00:12:01,817 --> 00:12:04,550
Enough. Stop questioning and just head straight.

190
00:12:05,583 --> 00:12:07,150
Would you consider...

191
00:12:07,150 --> 00:12:08,450
a business partnership with me?

192
00:12:08,450 --> 00:12:10,950
Enough. Stop questioning and just head straight.

193
00:12:14,683 --> 00:12:16,217
Do what?

194
00:12:16,217 --> 00:12:17,817
Partnership?

195
00:12:18,517 --> 00:12:20,150
Yes.

196
00:12:23,883 --> 00:12:27,050
Did you just propose a partnership to me?

197
00:12:27,050 --> 00:12:28,683
Yes.

198
00:12:30,850 --> 00:12:34,417
What's your scheme?

199
00:12:34,417 --> 00:12:37,450
You know...

200
00:12:37,450 --> 00:12:39,383
what that partnership means, right?

201
00:12:39,383 --> 00:12:42,117
Sure, it means working together.

202
00:12:43,117 --> 00:12:46,250
[Dorothy]

203
00:12:48,717 --> 00:12:50,650
You said you need to move out of your old place.

204
00:12:50,650 --> 00:12:52,617
Last time you moved the company office,

205
00:12:52,617 --> 00:12:55,617
you even sold the Bundang house
you got from your parents, right?

206
00:12:55,617 --> 00:12:57,517
Jeez, you're an old man now

207
00:12:57,517 --> 00:12:59,917
with no house at all.

208
00:12:59,917 --> 00:13:02,283
Whether I give up the old house

209
00:13:02,283 --> 00:13:04,117
or sell the Bundang one,

210
00:13:04,117 --> 00:13:06,583
you shouldn't be acting like this.

211
00:13:07,683 --> 00:13:10,017
Pass this to your finance director.

212
00:13:10,017 --> 00:13:12,450
Please deliver this to Ms. Yoo Ha Na, Mr. O.

213
00:13:12,450 --> 00:13:14,250
What?

214
00:13:14,250 --> 00:13:16,450
I'm currently lending money
at high interest rates.

215
00:13:16,450 --> 00:13:18,983
The interest is due at the end of the month,

216
00:13:20,550 --> 00:13:23,750
so please don't be late with
the payment, Mr. O Sang Sik.

217
00:13:33,883 --> 00:13:35,483
Ms. Yoo.

218
00:13:50,617 --> 00:13:52,617
What's this?

219
00:13:52,617 --> 00:13:56,283
Why did you borrow money without telling me?

220
00:13:59,550 --> 00:14:01,750
You told me to try borrowing money somewhere.

221
00:14:01,750 --> 00:14:05,383
Didn't you suggest solving
the overdue office rent?

222
00:14:06,383 --> 00:14:07,483
Well, that's...

223
00:14:07,483 --> 00:14:09,117
How would the bank trust our company enough

224
00:14:09,117 --> 00:14:10,483
to lend us money?

225
00:14:10,483 --> 00:14:11,750
What else do we have but private loans?

226
00:14:11,750 --> 00:14:14,017
Well, that's true. But...

227
00:14:14,017 --> 00:14:16,117
Are you angry about borrowing money?

228
00:14:16,117 --> 00:14:18,222
Or is it because you borrowed from Ms. Yang?

229
00:14:18,222 --> 00:14:19,350
What?

230
00:14:19,350 --> 00:14:22,450
If you're upset about the loan,
we already discussed this.

231
00:14:22,450 --> 00:14:24,350
If you're mad I borrowed from Ms. Yang,

232
00:14:24,350 --> 00:14:26,217
you should've told me not to borrow from her

233
00:14:26,217 --> 00:14:28,583
in advance.

234
00:14:32,850 --> 00:14:35,250
If you want to protect your pride, do it properly.

235
00:14:35,250 --> 00:14:37,217
If you want to succeed, abandon your pride.

236
00:14:37,217 --> 00:14:38,783
Choose one or the other.

237
00:14:38,783 --> 00:14:41,417
Don't try to have the best of both worlds.

238
00:14:50,283 --> 00:14:53,183
Ugh, this is so awkward and embarrassing.

239
00:14:54,017 --> 00:14:55,617
Well,

240
00:14:55,617 --> 00:14:57,450
I'm...

241
00:14:57,450 --> 00:15:00,583
Am I just trying to have the best of both worlds?

242
00:15:04,217 --> 00:15:05,650
Oh, Ms. Yoo, where are you going?

243
00:15:05,650 --> 00:15:07,583
I'm taking a half-day leave.

244
00:15:09,617 --> 00:15:12,383
Ah, I envy Yeo Reum.

245
00:15:12,383 --> 00:15:14,983
Her travel timing is impeccable.

246
00:15:17,550 --> 00:15:21,450
He was just really exasperated.

247
00:15:21,450 --> 00:15:22,750
See?

248
00:15:22,750 --> 00:15:24,950
I told you it wouldn't go well.

249
00:15:24,950 --> 00:15:27,517
Mr. O isn't that easygoing.

250
00:15:27,517 --> 00:15:31,050
He can arrange funds
anywhere. What's the big deal?

251
00:15:31,050 --> 00:15:32,650
I guess he doesn't like it.

252
00:15:32,650 --> 00:15:34,317
The money borrowed from his ex-wife.

253
00:15:34,317 --> 00:15:36,683
Ugh, such pathetic pride.

254
00:15:36,683 --> 00:15:39,383
Why is he still clinging to that?

255
00:15:40,917 --> 00:15:43,417
Is there such a thing as a noble pride

256
00:15:43,417 --> 00:15:45,883
and a wretched pride?

257
00:15:45,883 --> 00:15:49,650
How else could he survive
in this industry without pride?

258
00:15:49,650 --> 00:15:51,117
Thanks to that pride,

259
00:15:51,117 --> 00:15:53,183
our company avoided messy rumors

260
00:15:53,183 --> 00:15:56,017
and stayed upright all this time.

261
00:15:57,183 --> 00:15:59,217
Yes.

262
00:15:59,217 --> 00:16:01,950
Right, exactly.

263
00:16:03,350 --> 00:16:05,050
That's true.

264
00:16:05,050 --> 00:16:07,950
[Jangteo Restaurant]

265
00:16:07,950 --> 00:16:10,183
You're looking for someone?

266
00:16:10,183 --> 00:16:12,217
Yes.

267
00:16:12,217 --> 00:16:15,083
Is there someone you know here?

268
00:16:15,083 --> 00:16:16,550
Describe the person.

269
00:16:16,550 --> 00:16:18,217
I need details to help search.

270
00:16:18,217 --> 00:16:19,917
Well...

271
00:16:22,150 --> 00:16:25,083
<i>Her hair was tied up,</i>

272
00:16:25,083 --> 00:16:27,317
<i>with a slightly intimidating expression.</i>

273
00:16:27,317 --> 00:16:30,750
What are you saying?

